NAVIGATION — SCROLL INTO VIEW
Navigation scrolls BOTH panes to the target row.
In WorkspaceLayout or App:
typescriptconst rowRefsA = useRef<(HTMLTableRowElement | null)[]>([])
const rowRefsB = useRef<(HTMLTableRowElement | null)[]>([])

function navigateTo(pos: number) {
  setCurrentChangeIndex(pos)
  const targetRow = changeIndex[pos]
  rowRefsA.current[targetRow]?.scrollIntoView({
    behavior: 'smooth',
    block: 'center',
  })
  // scrollRefB will sync via scroll listener automatically
  // no need to scroll B explicitly
}
Scroll B syncs automatically via the scroll listener.
Only need to scroll A explicitly.

